# Service Booking Platform (Week 9)

## Overview

The Service Booking Platform is a full-stack MERN (MongoDB, Express, React, Node.js) application that allows users to browse professional services, create bookings, make demo payments, and receive email/SMS notifications. It includes a customer dashboard, an admin dashboard, and Week 9 performance and security optimizations.

## Features

- User Registration & Login
- Professional Service Listing
- Service Booking
- Customer Dashboard
- Admin Dashboard
- Payment Integration (Demo)
- Email Notifications
- SMS Notifications
- Performance Optimization
- Security Enhancements

## Tech Stack

- React.js
- Node.js
- Express.js
- MongoDB
- Mongoose
- Axios
- Nodemailer
- Twilio
- Vercel (frontend hosting)
- Render (backend hosting)

## Installation

```bash
git clone <repository-url>
cd service-booking-platform
npm install
```

### Backend

```bash
cd backend
npm install
npm start
```

### Frontend

```bash
cd frontend/frontend
npm install
npm run dev
```

## Environment Variables

Create a `.env` file in the backend directory with the following variables:

```
MONGO_URI=
JWT_SECRET=
EMAIL_USER=
EMAIL_PASS=
TWILIO_SID=
TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN=
TWILIO_PHONE=
```

