## API Endpoints

| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|---|---|---|
| POST | /api/auth/register | Register a new user |
| POST | /api/auth/login | User login |
| GET | /api/services | Get all services |
| POST | /api/bookings | Create booking |
| GET | /api/bookings | Get all bookings |
| POST | /api/payments/create-order | Create demo payment order |
| POST | /api/payments/verify | Verify payment |
| GET | /health | Server health check |

## Performance Optimizations

- React Lazy Loading (`React.lazy` + `Suspense`)
- `React.memo` to prevent unnecessary re-renders
- `useMemo` to cache computed values
- `useCallback` to prevent unnecessary function recreation
- Backend caching with `node-cache`
- MongoDB `.lean()` queries for faster execution
- MongoDB indexes for improved search performance
- Compression middleware to reduce API response size

## Security Features

- Helmet for secure HTTP headers
- CORS to restrict cross-origin requests
- Rate limiting to prevent abuse
- XSS protection
- JWT authentication
- Password hashing with bcrypt
- Environment variables for sensitive credentials
- MongoDB Atlas with secured network access
- HTTPS deployment on Render & Vercel

